{
  "texts": [
    "We test the algorithmic initialization in a wide range of B 0 from 1 T down to 25 mT.",
    "The results at different stages of the protocol are seen in Fig. 2a It is also important to assess the time cost for the algorithmic initialization, as it involves multiple control and readout iterations.",
    "The table in Extended Data Fig. 3b breaks down the time spent on control and readout.",
    "We see that the readout integration time t integration dominates the time consumption.",
    "At B 0 = 85 mT and T = 1 K, the full algorithmic initialization takes an average of around three iterations, which totals around 150 μs."
  ]
}